+## Idea
+
+Given two
+[families with descent data](synthetic-homotopy-theory.families-descent-data-pushouts.md)
+for [pushouts](synthetic-homotopy-theory.pushouts.md) `P ‚âà (PA, PB, PS)` and
+`Q ‚âà (QA, QB, QS)`, we show that fiberwise maps `(x : X) ‚Üí P x ‚Üí Q x` correspond
+to [morphisms](synthetic-homotopy-theory.morphisms-descent-data-pushouts.md)
+`(PA, PB, PS) ‚Üí (QA, QB, QS)`.
+
+**Proof:** We first characterize the type family `x ‚Ü¶ P x ‚Üí Q x`. The
+corresponding [descent data](synthetic-homotopy-theory.descent-data-pushouts.md)
+consists of the type families
+
+```text
+  a ‚Ü¶ PA a ‚Üí QA a
+  b ‚Ü¶ PB b ‚Üí QB b,
+```
+
+and the gluing data sending `h : PA (fs) ‚Üí QA (fs)` to
+`(QS s ‚àò h ‚àò (PS s)‚Åª¬π) : PB (gs) ‚Üí QB (gs)`.
+
+The fiberwise families then correspond to
+[sections](synthetic-homotopy-theory.sections-descent-data-pushouts.md) of this
+descent data, and it suffices to show that those correspond to morphisms. The
+coherence datum of such a section has the type
+
+```text
+  (s : S) ‚Üí QS s ‚àò sA (fs) ‚àò (PS s)‚Åª¬π Ôºù sB (gs),
+```
+
+which we can massage into a coherence of the morphism as
+
+```text
+  QS s ‚àò sA (fs) ‚àò (PS s)‚Åª¬π = sB (gs)
+  ‚âÉ QS s ‚àò sA (fs) ‚àò (PS s)‚Åª¬π ~ sB (gs)  by function extensionality
+  ‚âÉ QS s ‚àò sA (fs) ~ sB (gs) ‚àò PS s      by transposition of (PS s)
+  ‚âÉ sB (gs) ‚àò PS s ~ QS s ‚àò sA (fs)      by symmetry of homotopies.
+```
